Package: telegram.ext
Type: Package
Title: Develop a Telegram Bot with R
Version: 0.7.0
Authors@R: person("Ernest", "Benedito", email = "ebeneditos@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Ernest Benedito <ebeneditos@gmail.com>
Description: This package features a number of tools to make the development of Telegram bots with R easy and straightforward. It is an extension of the 'telegram' package, an R wrapper around the Telegram Bot API (http://core.telegram.org/bots/api) that eases the access to Telegram's messaging facilities; and it is inspired by Python's submodule 'telegram.ext' from 'python-telegram-bot' library.
URL: http://github.com/ebeneditos/telegram.ext
BugReports: http://github.com/ebeneditos/telegram.ext/issues
Imports: R6, httr
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.3),
    telegram (>= 0.6.0)
License: LGPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
